g.text: UML Diagram: Class Organization in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.
a.xlink:title: ― StatisticalClassification: Set of categories represented by classification items where the subset of immediate children categories for any given parent category are mutually exclusive and jointly exhaustive with respect to that parent.

a.title: ― ContactInformation: Contact information for the individual or organization including location specification, address, web site, phone numbers, and other means of communication access. Address, location, telephone, and other means of communication can be repeated to express multiple means of a single type or change over ...
a.xlink:title: ― ContactInformation: Contact information for the individual or organization including location specification, address, web site, phone numbers, and other means of communication access. Address, location, telephone, and other means of communication can be repeated to express multiple means of a single type or change over ...

a.title: ― OrganizationName: Names by which the organization is known. Use the attribute isFormal with a value of True to designate the legal or formal name of the organization. Names may be typed with typeOfOrganizationName to indicate their appropriate usage.
a.xlink:title: ― OrganizationName: Names by which the organization is known. Use the attribute isFormal with a value of True to designate the legal or formal name of the organization. Names may be typed with typeOfOrganizationName to indicate their appropriate usage.

a.title: ― Agent: Actor that performs a role in relation to a process or product.
a.xlink:title: ― Agent: Actor that performs a role in relation to a process or product.

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.
a.xlink:title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: ― Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: ― PrivateImage: References an image using the standard Image description. In addition to the standard attributes provides an effective date (period) and a privacy ranking.
a.xlink:title: ― PrivateImage: References an image using the standard Image description. In addition to the standard attributes provides an effective date (period) and a privacy ranking.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
a.xlink:title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...

a.title: ― AgentPosition: Assigns a sequence number to an agent in an agent listing.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentPosition: Assigns a sequence number to an agent in an agent listing.

a.title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentListing: Listing of agents of any type who may be organized to describe relationships between agents.

a.title: ― isMaintainedBy: Organization, agency, or group within an agency responsible for the maintenance and upkeep of the statistical classification.
a.xlink:title: ― isMaintainedBy: Organization, agency, or group within an agency responsible for the maintenance and upkeep of the statistical classification.

a.title: ― isMaintainedBy: The unit or group of persons within the organization responsible for the agent listing (i.e., for adding, changing or deleting agent entries).
a.xlink:title: ― isMaintainedBy: The unit or group of persons within the organization responsible for the agent listing (i.e., for adding, changing or deleting agent entries).
